umbent Won*\n*   **Wisconsin:** Tammy Baldwin (D) - *Incumbent Won*\n*   **Wyoming:** John Barrasso (R) - *Incumbent Won*\n\n**Special Elections:**\n\n*   **Minnesota:** Tina Smith (D) - *Incumbent Won* (Appointed to fill Al Franken's seat after his resignation)\n*   **Mississippi:** Cindy Hyde-Smith (R) - *Incumbent Won* (Appointed to fill Thad Cochran's seat after his resignation)\n\n**Key takeaways:**\n\n*   Democrats were defending a large number of seats, particularly in states that had voted for Donald Trump in 2016.\n*   Republicans aimed to expand their majority in the Senate.\n*   The results of these elections significantly impacted the balance of power in the Senate.\n",
